# UI Polish & System Rework — Setup Walkthrough

## Summary of Changes

| # | Change | Files Modified/Created |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Room selection panel + fade transition | `RoomSwitcherUI.cs` (rewritten), `ScreenFader.cs` (new) |
| 2 | Food/water bowls as grid furniture | `FoodBowl.cs`, `WaterBowl.cs`, `CatAI.cs` |
| 3 | Claim buttons for tasks & achievements | `DailyTaskManager.cs`, `DailyTaskUI.cs`, `AchievementManager.cs`, `AchievementUI.cs`, `GameData.cs` |
| 4 | Grid layout (4 items/row) for shop & inventory | *(Unity Editor change — see instructions below)* |
| 5 | Click-to-lock furniture placement | `FurniturePlacementUI.cs` (rewritten) |
| 6 | Fishing mini-game as UI overlay | `CatFishingGame.cs` (rewritten), `FishUI.cs` (new), `FishSpawner.cs` (rewritten) |

---

## 1. Room Selection Panel + Fade Transition

### ScreenFader Setup
1. In Canvas, create an **Image** named "ScreenFade"
   - Color: **black** (0, 0, 0, 0) — starts transparent
   - Stretch to fill entire screen
   - Raycast Target: **off** (script manages this)
   - Set **Sibling Order** to last (renders on top)
2. Create a **ScreenFader** GameObject → add `ScreenFader` component
3. Assign the black Image to `Fade Image`

### Room Selector Panel
Replace the old left/right arrows with:
```
📁 Canvas
└── 📁 RoomSelectionPanel (hidden by default)
    ├── 📜 RoomSwitcherUI (script)
    ├── 📝 Title — "Select Room"
    ├── 📁 ScrollView → Content (VerticalLayoutGroup)
    └── 🔘 CloseButton — "✕"
```

**Room Slot Prefab**: Create a Button with:
- `TMP_Text[0]` — room name
- `TMP_Text[1]` — status ("Current" / "Go" / "🔒 500 🐾")
- Optional `CanvasGroup` for dimming locked/current rooms

Add a **"🏠 Rooms"** HUD button that calls `RoomSwitcherUI.Open()`.

---

## 2. Food & Water Bowls as Grid Furniture

In the Inspector for **FoodBowl** and **WaterBowl**:

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Grid Position | The iso grid cell where the bowl sits (e.g. `(2, 3)`) |
| Grid Size | `(1, 1)` — bowls occupy 1 tile |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Position the bowl GameObject** so its world position matches `IsometricGrid.GridToWorld(gridPosition)`. The bowl registers itself on the grid at Start and releases on Destroy.

The **cat walks to the nearest walkable tile adjacent to the bowl** to eat/drink — it no longer walks directly onto the bowl's tile.

---

## 3. Claim System for Daily Tasks & Achievements

### Daily Tasks — Claim Flow
Tasks are now **completed** by game actions but **rewards require pressing "Claim"**.

**Task Slot Prefab** needs:
- `nameText` (TMP) — task name
- `rewardText` (TMP) — "+20 🐾"
- `claimButton` (Button) — the interactable Claim/Claimed button
- `claimButtonText` (TMP) — on the button, shows "Claim", "Claimed", or "..."
- `checkmark` (Image) — color changes by state

### Achievements — Claim Flow
Achievement popup still appears when unlocked, but **rewards are only given after claiming** from the achievements list.

**List Item Prefab** needs:
- 3x `TMP_Text` — name, description, reward/status
- 1x `Button` — Claim button (shows "Claim", "Claimed", or "Locked")
- Optional `CanvasGroup` — for dimming locked items

### Red Dot Notifications
Both `DailyTaskUI` and `AchievementUI` have a **`hudRedDot`** field:
- Create a small red circle Image (10-15px) on the corner of the HUD button
- Assign it to the `hudRedDot` field
- It auto-shows when there are unclaimed rewards

```
📁 HUD
├── 🔘 TasksButton
│   └── 🔴 RedDot (Image, 12x12, red circle)
├── 🔘 AchievementsButton
│   └── 🔴 RedDot (Image, 12x12, red circle)
```

---

## 4. Grid Layout for Shop & Inventory (4 per row)

This is a **Unity Editor change** — replace `HorizontalLayoutGroup` with `GridLayoutGroup`:

### Shop Panel Content
1. Select the **ScrollView → Content** under ShopPanel
2. **Remove** `HorizontalLayoutGroup`
3. **Add** `GridLayoutGroup` with:

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Cell Size | `(150, 180)` — adjust to your item card size |
| Spacing | `(10, 10)` |
| Start Corner | Upper Left |
| Start Axis | Horizontal |
| Constraint | Fixed Column Count |
| Constraint Count | `4` |

4. Make sure the Content also has `ContentSizeFitter`:
   - Vertical Fit: **Preferred Size**

### Inventory Panel Content (Furniture Placement)
Same steps on the **inventoryContent** ScrollView Content:
- `GridLayoutGroup` with ConstraintCount = `4`
- `ContentSizeFitter` with Vertical Fit = Preferred Size

---

## 5. Click-to-Lock Furniture Placement

New 3-state flow:

```
┌────────────┐    click valid    ┌────────────┐    Confirm     ┌────────────┐
│  Following  │ ──── tile ────→  │   Locked    │ ───────────→  │   Placed   │
│ (ghost      │                  │ (ghost      │               │ (real      │
│  tracks     │                  │  stays      │    Cancel     │  furniture)|
│  cursor)    │ ←── Cancel ────  │  in place)  │ ───────────→  │            │
└────────────┘                   └────────────┘               └────────────┘
```

- **Following**: Ghost snaps to isometric grid tiles as cursor moves. Grid highlights show valid/invalid.
- **Click valid tile**: Ghost **locks** at that position. Color changes to `lockedColor`. Confirm button appears.
- **Confirm**: Places furniture permanently. **Cancel**: Destroys ghost, back to inventory.

> [!TIP]
> The ghost **does not follow the mouse** when hovering over UI buttons. Only clicks on grid tiles (not over UI) trigger the lock.

---

## 6. Fishing Mini-Game as UI Overlay

### Old vs New

| Aspect | Before | After |
|---|---|---|
| Fish rendering | World-space SpriteRenderer | UI Image (Canvas) |
| Tap detection | Physics2D.OverlapPoint | IPointerClickHandler (UI) |
| Spawning area | World coordinates | RectTransform |
| Cat interaction | Still active | **Disabled** while playing |

### FishUI Prefab Setup
1. Create a UI element (Image) → name "FishUI"
2. Add components: `Image`, `Button`, `FishUI`
3. Size: ~60×30 (adjust to your fish art)
4. **Save as Prefab**

### Mini-Game Panel Setup
```
📁 Canvas
└── 📁 MiniGamePanel (hidden, full-screen overlay)
    ├── 📜 CatFishingGame (script)
    ├── 📁 FishArea (stretch to fill, this is where fish swim)
    │   └── 📜 FishSpawner (script)
    ├── 📝 ScoreText — "0"
    ├── 📝 TimerText — "30s"
    ├── 📝 InstructionText
    ├── 🔘 StartButton — "Start!"
    ├── 🔘 CloseButton — "✕"
    ├── 🖼️ CatPawUI (RectTransform, hidden by default)
    └── 📁 GameOverPanel (hidden)
        ├── 📝 FinalScoreText
        ├── 📝 CoinsEarnedText
        ├── 🔘 PlayAgainButton
        └── 🔘 ExitButton
```

### FishSpawner Configuration

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Fish UI Prefab | Your FishUI prefab |
| Fish Area | The "FishArea" RectTransform |
| Normal Fish Sprite | Your fish sprite |
| Golden Fish Sprite | Your golden fish sprite |
| Base Speed | 250 (pixels/sec) |
| Max Speed | 500 (pixels/sec) |

> [!WARNING]
> The old `Fish.cs` (world-space) is now unused. You can delete it and its prefab. The new `FishUI.cs` replaces it entirely.

### Interaction Blocking
When the mini-game opens, it **automatically disables** `CatInteraction` and `CatAI` so the player can focus on fishing without accidentally petting the cat or tapping the ground.

